#: ../../source/repeatable-processes/work-with-tasks.rst:21
msgid ""
"You can automatically complete tasks in a playbook run using keyword "
"triggers. When the keywords you've entered are mentioned in the run, the "
"task is marked as completed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/repeatable-processes/work-with-tasks.rst:23
msgid ""
"For this feature, you should use a string of text rather than individual "
"words. The search is an ``ANY`` search, meaning that if you used the "
"individual words \"target\" and \"completed\", either of those words will"
" trigger the action to be marked as complete. If you're using phrases "
"that have formatting, make sure you use the Markdown formatting in the "
"text field."
